ACCIDENTAL RELEASE PREVENTION AND EMERGENCY RESPONSE POLICIES



Compass Chemical International is committed to worker and public safety and to the protection of the environment.  We are committed to operating and maintaining all of our processes in a safe and responsible manner, as demonstrated by the resources we invest to prevent accidents.  In addition to ensuring that our employees have the best training in the operation of our processes, we demand that safety be the first priority in the design, installation, operation and maintenance of our processes.

It is the policy of Compass Chemical International to manufacture and distribute materials with minimal impact on the environment and without injury to our employees, customers, and community.  To that end, Compass Chemical Internationl is committed to:



The protection of the health, safety, and security of our employees and facilities;

Complying with all applicable federal, state and local Environmental, Health, Safety, and Security regulations and our other related voluntary requirements.

Continual reduction of the impact of our operations on the environment through ongoing pollution prevention programs;

Continual communications and openness with our stakeholders;

Training all employees regarding the importance of EHS&S protection and roles they play as stewards.



